Definition: Christianity) any of about 70 theologians in the period from the 2nd to the 7th century whose writing established and confirmed official church doctrine
Example: in the Roman Catholic Church some were later declared saints and became Doctor of the Church; the best known Latin Church Fathers are Ambrose, Augustine, Gregory the Great, and Jerome; those who wrote in Greek include Athanasius, Basil, Gregory Nazianzen, and John Chrysostom
Synonyms: Father_of_the_Church, Father, theologian, noun, cognition, Christianity, c, any, of, about, theologians, in, the, period, from, nd, to, th, century, whose, writing, established, and, confirmed, official, church, doctrine, Roman, Catholic, Church, some, were, later, declared, saints, became, Doctor, best, known, Latin, Fathers, are, Ambrose, Augustine, Gregory, Great, Jerome, those, who, wrote, Greek, include, Athanasius, Basil, Nazianzen, John, Chrysostom
Category: noun.person
